    • Class jparsec.ephem.EphemerisElement extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • targetBody

          Target.TARGET targetBody
          Planet ID for ephemeris, probe index value when calculation orbits or probes, or satellite index for orbits of artificial satellites.

        • equinox

          double equinox
          Set equinox of the results as a Julian day in Terrestrial Time.

        • isTopocentric

          boolean isTopocentric
          True for topocentric ephemeris, false for geocentric.

        • ephemMethod

          EphemerisElement.REDUCTION_METHOD ephemMethod
          Methods for Greenwich Mean Sidereal Time, Precession, and Obliquity. Please read the documentation in each value to choose the adequate one.

        • frame

          EphemerisElement.FRAME frame
          Defines the frame reference of the results.

        • ephemType

          EphemerisElement.COORDINATES_TYPE ephemType
          Type of output coordinates. You should choose apparent coordinates almost always.

        • algorithm

          EphemerisElement.ALGORITHM algorithm
          Algorithm to apply for the calculation. This field is necessary when calling in a general way to Ephem.getEphemeris(jparsec.time.TimeElement, jparsec.observer.ObserverElement, EphemerisElement, boolean), which is the recommendend procedure. Please read the documentation in each parameter to choose the adequate one.

        • orbit

          OrbitalElement orbit
          Holds the orbital elements of a given body.

        • wavelength

          EphemerisElement.OBSERVING_WAVELENGTH wavelength
          The observing wavelength. Default value is optical with Bennet (1982) refraction model.

        • correctEquatorialCoordinatesForRefraction

          boolean correctEquatorialCoordinatesForRefraction
          True to correct output right ascension and declination for local refraction effects, and equinox based calculations, in case coordinates are topocentric and apparent. Default value is false.

        • correctForExtinction

          boolean correctForExtinction
          Extinction correction flag for equinox based calculations. If set to true, in every ephemerides calculation with topocentric results and apparent coordinates the apparent magnitude will be corrected for extinction (only in that case, topocentric plus apparent). Default value is false to keep always the same value for the output magnitude.

        • useVondrak2011PrecessionFormulaInsteadOfIAU2006

          boolean useVondrak2011PrecessionFormulaInsteadOfIAU2006
          Sets the precession model to that of Vondrák et al. 2011 (see A&A 534, A22) instead of the original IAU2006 model by Capitaine et al. 2003. This affects the calculation of precession for reduction algorithms IAU2006 and IAU2009. The effect is a correct output for dates very far from J2000 epoch. IAU model should not be used 10 000 years far from J2000. Vondrák parameterization allows to reach up to 200 000 years far from J2000, with an error in the degree level. Default value is equals to the value of EphemerisElement.ALLOW_VONDRAK_PRECESSION, which is true at startup. Set this value to false to use the original IAU model, or the mentioned static variable to use always the original IAU model. Only for equinox based calculations.

        • correctForPolarMotion

          boolean correctForPolarMotion
          True (default value) to correct for pole motion using the Earth orientation parameters in equinox based calculations. Not supported in Android.

        • correctForEOP

          boolean correctForEOP
          Sets if Earth Orientation Parameters should be used to correct ephemerides for UT1 minus UTC time offset and the nutation components of the polar motion, in equinox based calculations. Default value is true. In case you change this value after computing ephemerides don't forget to call EarthOrientationParameters.clearEOP() and Nutation.clearPreviousCalculation().

        • correctEOPForDiurnalSubdiurnalTides

          boolean correctEOPForDiurnalSubdiurnalTides
          Sets if Earth Orientation Parameters should be corrected for diurnal and subdiurnal Earth tides, using the model by Ray 1994.

        • preferPrecisionInEphemerides

          boolean preferPrecisionInEphemerides
          Sets the prefer precision flag in ephemeris calculations. Default is true to allow maximum precision. Set to false to avoid this, resulting in (maybe) faster ephemeris, but generally with enough precision. Note that if you calculate ephemerides with JPL algorithms in a given date the performance could be better compared to setting this flag to false (which forces the Series96/Moshier methods). When calling ephemeris through Ephem.getEphemeris(jparsec.time.TimeElement, jparsec.observer.ObserverElement, jparsec.ephem.EphemerisElement, boolean, boolean) method the best possible algorithm will be used if this is set to true, although Moshier method is forced when JPL ephemeris files cannot be found and Series96 cannot be applied, so no dependency problems will appear, although the theory used could be different from the one selected in the ephemeris object.

          When this flag is set to false Moshier ephemerides can be used between years -3000 to +3000, with true the lower limit for inner planets is -1350.

          Distance from the Sun in Astronomical Units. Note that in certain methods (in fact, all of them except JPL ephemerides) the Sun is incorrectly assumed to be at the Solar System Barycenter (SSB), and this value is the distance to SSB, not to the Sun itsef.

          Another posible format to set a pointer in a given location (not towards a given point in the chart) is to replace the point number with '(x,y)' (without quotes), being x and y the pointer location in physical units.

        • pointersAngle

          ChartSeriesElement.POINTER_ANGLE pointersAngle
          Sets an angle in radians to point the pointers. Can be set to one of the constants defined in this class. Default value is up.

        • showArrowInPointers

          boolean showArrowInPointers
          To show or not arrows in pointers, yes by default.

        • showErrorBars

          boolean showErrorBars
          True (default) to show error bars.

        • pointersLabelOffsetFactor

          float pointersLabelOffsetFactor
          Sets the offset position factor for pointer labels. Should be between 0 and 2. 1 by default.

        • xMinimumValue

          double xMinimumValue
          Sets minimum value of x. Useful for charts in log scale where error bars can reach negative values.

        • yMinimumValue

          double yMinimumValue
          Sets minimum value of y. Useful for charts in log scale where error bars can reach negative values.

          True to enable (show) this series, false to hide it. This is only supported on xy charts.
